plan.rebalancing_guidelines:
Rebalance the portfolio annually at the end of each financial year. Maintain the core equity allocation (70% of the corpus) with the following sub-allocations:
- Large-Cap: 35% (HDFC Growth Fund)
- Mid-Cap: 15% (Motilal Oswal Midcap & HDFC Midcap Fund)
- Small-Cap: 25% (Motilal Oswal Equity Research & Advisor & Motilal Oswal Small Cap)

Adjust the percentages based on:
1. Underperformance (if any fund delivers less than 10% annualised return for two consecutive years);
2. Risk metrics (tracking error > 12%, Sharpe ratio < 1.0);
3. Fund manager changes or fund house restructuring;
4. Portfolio risk profile (equity exposure should never exceed 75% of total AUM);
5. Goals progress (if the corpus exceeds ₹12,000,000, reduce equity exposure to 50% and allocate the remaining 50% to gold ETFs and debt instruments).
